# Neon Sync Rush Privacy Policy

  Effective Date: June 23, 2026
  Last Updated: June 23, 2026

  [Operator Name] (“we,” “us,” or “our”) respects the privacy of Neon Sync Rush users. This Privacy Policy explains how information may be
  processed when you use the app.

  ## 1. Information Stored by the App

  Neon Sync Rush does not require registration or a user account. We do not operate a server that directly receives your personal
  information.

  The following information may be stored locally on your device:

  - Game scores and progress
  - Music and sound-effect settings
  - Haptic and gameplay settings
  - Input timing calibration
  - Guide completion status

  This information may be deleted when you uninstall the app or reset its data.

  ## 2. Advertising Information

  Neon Sync Rush uses Google AdMob to display advertisements.

  The Google Mobile Ads SDK may process information such as:

  - IP address and approximate location
  - Device or app identifiers
  - Advertisement views and interactions
  - App launches and user interactions
  - Crash logs, diagnostics, and performance information
  - Information used for personalized advertising when you provide consent

  The information processed may vary according to your location, device settings, consent choices, and Google’s policies.

  For more information, see:

  - Google Privacy Policy (https://policies.google.com/privacy)
  - How Google Uses Information from Sites or Apps That Use Its Services (https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites)

  ## 3. Purposes of Processing

  Information may be processed for the following purposes:

  - Providing game features and user settings
  - Providing personalized or non-personalized advertisements
  - Measuring advertising performance
  - Preventing fraud and security incidents
  - Diagnosing errors and improving app performance
  - Complying with applicable laws and platform policies

  ## 4. Consent and Privacy Choices

  Where required by law, Neon Sync Rush uses Google’s User Messaging Platform to present privacy and advertising consent options.

  You can review or change your choices from:

  Settings → Privacy Options

  You may continue using the game if you refuse or withdraw consent. However, non-personalized or limited advertisements may be displayed.

  ## 5. Data Retention and Deletion

  Game scores and settings are stored locally on your device. They may be removed when you uninstall the app.

  Information processed by Google AdMob is retained and deleted according to Google’s privacy and service policies.

  You may contact us using the details below if you have questions or requests concerning your information.

  ## 6. Third-Party Services and International Processing

  Neon Sync Rush uses services provided by Google LLC and its affiliates for advertising.

  Advertising information may be processed on servers located outside your country. The applicable processing locations, retention periods,
  and safeguards are governed by Google’s privacy and data-processing policies.

  We will update this Privacy Policy if additional advertising or analytics providers are introduced.

  ## 7. Children’s Privacy

  Neon Sync Rush does not knowingly collect personal information from children below the applicable age of digital consent without
  authorization from a parent or legal guardian.

  If you believe that a child’s personal information has been processed improperly, contact us so that we can investigate and take
  appropriate action.

  ## 8. Your Rights

  Depending on applicable law, you may have the right to:

  - Confirm whether your personal information is being processed
  - Request access to, correction of, or deletion of your information
  - Withdraw consent for data processing or personalized advertising
  - Object to certain processing activities

  Advertising privacy choices can be changed through the app’s Privacy Options menu.

  ## 9. Security

  We minimize the information directly processed by the app and store game settings and progress locally whenever possible.

  However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet can be guaranteed to be completely secure.

  ## 10. Changes to This Privacy Policy

  We may update this Privacy Policy when applicable laws, app features, or third-party services change.

  Material changes will be announced through the app or this webpage. The revised policy will apply from the effective date shown above.

